<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871006-0172 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Copperweld Corp.</HL><DD> 10/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> COS </IN><TEXT>   COPPERWELD CORP. said it has completed two unsecured credit facilities valued at $15 million at prime interest rates with two commercial banks. Copperweld said it has a $10 million, three-year revolving credit agreement with Pittsburgh National Bank and a $5 million, one-year line of credit with National Bank of Detroit. The Pittsburgh specialty steelmaker said it has no current plans to borrow under the facilities. </TEXT></DOC>